notes: ST Jayasuriya's 151* regains him the best individual ODI score by a Sri Lankan. PA de Silva previously took the record off him with 145 v Kenya at Kandy in 1995-96 after Jayasuriya held it with 140 v New Zealand at Bloemfontein in 1994-95. He now also simultaneously holds the best batting and bowling figures in ODIs by a Sri Lankan with his 6-29 v England at Colombo in 1992-93.

milestones.description: Romesh Kaluwitharana has broken the record for most ducks (13) in ODIs for SL, going past Gurusinha's 12
Jayasuriya's 151 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for SL), surpassing de Silva's 145
